commit.message:
Add an [exec_partial_detailed] function to re. (#219)

This allows users to see the groups that matched if a match
exists for [exec_partial], and if not, then it tells you
an index before which a match cannot exist.

commit.message:
Simplify main loop

It was optimized for the x86 architecture. Modern architectures have
plenty of registers, so we can use a simpler loop.

Color maps: Switch from bytes to string

These tables are not mutated.

doc(Re.Posix): render main doc comment

Odoc on ocaml.org is not rendering the main doc comment.
Remove the 2nd doc comment and then at least Re.Posix renders it,
but the main module still doesn't.

TODO: is this a dune or odoc bug?

Suggested-By: Pau Ruiz Safont <pau.safont@citrix.com>
